comments: Curry (GSW) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Richardson's (BOS) arm that affects his play at the basket.
Smart (BOS) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Both Curry (GSW) and Williams III (BOS) engage and then disengage in arm contact underneath while trying to gain rebound position.
Brown (BOS) makes marginal contact with Curry's (GSW) body during his shooting motion that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Green (GSW) makes marginal contact with Brown's (BOS) body during his shooting motion that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Williams III (BOS) is deemed to be imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Iguodala (GSW) reaches in and cleanly dislodges the ball from Brown (BOS) at the end of his drive.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: The ball makes contact with Brown's (BOS) lower body last before it goes OOB.
Brown (BOS) makes contact to the arm of Curry (GSW) that affects his SQBR.
Smart (BOS) is not established in a legal guarding position in Curry's (GSW) path at the time of the contact and a defensive foul should be called.
Wiggins (GSW) legally contests Tatum's (BOS) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.

Brown (BOS) makes incidental contact to Green's (GSW) head/face area while he pursues the rebound. Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Correctly called delay of game on the Warriors.
Richardson (BOS) commits a take foul on Lee (GSW).
